      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-6 mt-6 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 1 – Monday, March 13th – Friday, March 17th</h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">My first week here in OPEC have been very exciting and nervous at the same time. In our first week all activities are all related to the Briefing and Orientations. We were of course introduce to the company’s type of work, rules and regulation, and It’s policies. We were also introduce to Japanese Manner and language as this company OPEC is a Japanese company esepecializong in engineering mostly CAD works for Japanese clients. Also, as we were introduce to our department where we are assign to, they gave me manual and introduce me about their process. In the fourth day I was given a practice which is a 2D exercise using JW CAD and in the fifth day I was given another practice this time it’s’ in 3D. </p>
      
      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-6 mt-6 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 2 – Monday, March 20th – Friday, March 24th</h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week two has been an adjusting time transinioning from introduction phase to actual work and processess. On monday and Tuesday I was given another practice or test for them to know my skill in visualization as they give me some 3D exercises for me to make using JWCAD. On the following day,My department and staff started introducing me to the actual process which is the Jikugumizu Process or House Frame Drawing and then gave me some sample projects to work with. </p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-6 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 3 – Monday, March 27th – Friday, March 31st</h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On this day My department just gave me some practice projects to work with, with one of which is an actual project they made last time for a Japanese client. On this week I just continue learning the process especially the commands as the software used is in Japanese language and the interface is kinda hard as it’s my first time using CAD. So with the given project I just continue familiarizing the commands using manual and asking question to my teammate.  </p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 4 – Monday, April 03rd – Friday, April 07th </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Within this week as the philippines have its holiday wich is holy week and we do just have three days of work from Monday to Wednesday, I just given another set of activity which is a Jikuguzimu project or house frame drawing.</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 5 – Monday, April 10th – Friday, April 14th </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">This week as the philippines have its holiday wich is holy week aduring this Monday only, I just continue making Jikuguzimu project or house frame drawing.</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 6 – Monday, April 17th – Friday, April 21st </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On week five as I continue making different practice projects I was given another set of project wich is different and with another process which is single item drawing. With this I was given four different projects for me to familiarize the process. </p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 7 – Monday, April 24th – Friday, April 28th </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">This week was one of the highlight of my OJT or internship here as I was given an actual project. For the first three days I was given another set of project which named Color 81 project and on Thursday and Friday I was given an actual project named Banjar Forest Villa which is we need to make a single item process drawing.</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 8 – Monday, May 01st – Friday, May 05th </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">For the first week of May there will be a series of event in school as this week the Holy Cross will be hosting MCITS or Mindanao Conference for Information Technolgy Society. </p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 9 – Monday, May 08th – Friday, May 12th</h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On this week I just continue making and double check my works on the actual project which is the Banjar Forest Villa Actual project and also on this week we were given some spare time to make and prioritize our time to make a power point presentation for the coming company report or presentation of what are the learnings and takeaways as we work as internhere at OPEC.</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 10 – Monday, May 15th – Friday, May 19th  </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On this week of May as we have a scheduled company presentation next week for all the learnings and experiences with the company, we have given time to prepare our self and prepare a powerpoint presentation for next week’s presentation. On thursday and Friday this week conducted our retreat a tradition on our school HCDC especially catholic school to have this event where in student have a chance and a time to get closer to GOD. This occasion also gave us a change to refelect on our lives and hav a little bonding or time with friends and classmates. </p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 11 – Monday, May 22nd – Friday, May 26th </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify"data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On the fourth day of May our company has this event where OJTees or interns should present their or our learning and experiences in this company with the presence of the company’s president “”. Along with this week also, The most anticipated event for BSIT and CPE students will be held whish is Techno Fair showcasing our different capstone projects. This event evaluate our capstone projects with judges and spectators mostly student from lower years to get some ideas and inspiration</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-10 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 12 – Monday, May 29th – Friday, June 02nd </h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">On this day as our last days as intern here in OPEC is approaching, I now focus on making or developing our System Project which is A QR Code based Date and Time Record Management Systemas a requirement for our Practicum subject. On the next day there is one project that is given to the team which all staff of SHINOHARA department get involve for trying to recreate KEIHOKU PRECUT LOGO using JWCAD. After I made my version of it, I can now focus on my other school requirements by compiling all the requirements. Along with developing my porfolio website using laravel.</p>

      <h1 class="sm:text-2xl text-xl font-medium title-font text-gray-200 mb-6 mt-10 text-center" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Week 13 – Monday, June 05th – Friday, June 09th</h1>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-xl text-justify" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom">Last week of my OJT or internship here at OPEC, we ere given the time to focus on our other school works or paper works especially on our project system.</p>

